The paper discusses an approximation to backpropagation algorithm for training deep neural networks using synapses implemented with memristors. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.EM (Electromagnetics), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). However, given the focus on neural networks and synaptic plasticity, cs.NE is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because they involve hardware implementation, circuit design, and signal processing, which are important aspects of memristor-based neural networks.
